text:
Q: The widget Link shows the url of other widget on the page A: <p>If you already use <code>launchUrl</code>, you don’t actually <em>need</em> <code>Link</code></p>
<pre><code>InkWell(
  onTap: () =&gt; launchUrl(
    Uri.parse(absolutePath),
    mode: LaunchMode.inAppWebView,
  ),
  onSecondaryTap: () async {
    await Clipboard.setData(ClipboardData(text: absolutePath));
  },
  child: MouseRegion(
    cursor: SystemMouseCursors.click,
    child: child,
  ),
);
</code></pre>
